actions.comment:
Thanks for the detailed report and attached image. This is a known pattern where specific JPEG images can't be decoded by Skia's native codec — we have several related reports (#2359, #2347, #1621).

To get more diagnostic info, you can use the `SKCodecResult` overload:

```csharp
var codec = SKCodec.Create(stream, out SKCodecResult result);
if (codec == null)
    Console.WriteLine($"Codec creation failed: {result}");
```

As a workaround, you can pre-process the image with another library (e.g., SixLabors.ImageSharp) to re-encode it as PNG before passing to SkiaSharp.

We'll investigate whether SkiaSharp 3.x (with updated Skia) handles this image correctly.
